uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.model

Class Assay

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.model.IndexedElement
      • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.model.Assay

  • public class Assay
extends IndexedElement
    The application of a measurement about the sample (in this case through MS) - producing values about small molecules, peptides or proteins. One assay is typically mapped to one MS run in the case of label-free MS analysis or multiple assays are mapped to one MS run for multiplexed techniques, along with a description of the label or tag applied. User: Qingwei Date: 23/05/13

      • addQuantificationModSite

        public void addQuantificationModSite(java.lang.Integer id,
                            java.lang.String site)
        assay[1-n]-quantification_mod[1-n]-site: A string describing the modifications site. Following the unimod convention, modification site is a residue (e.g. "M"), terminus ("N-term" or "C-term") or both (e.g. "N-term Q" or "C-term K").
        Parameters:
        id - a non-negative integer number.
        site - a non MZTabUtils.isEmpty(String) String.

      • addQuantificationModPosition

        public void addQuantificationModPosition(java.lang.Integer id,
                                java.lang.String position)
        assay[1-n]-quantification_mod[1-n]-position: A string describing the term specifity of the modification. Following the unimod convention, term specifity is denoted by the strings "Anywhere", "Any N-term", "Any C-term", "Protein N-term", "Protein C-term".
        Parameters:
        id - a non-negative integer number.
        position - a non MZTabUtils.isEmpty(String) String.
